Outcome:
1.1/ Lack of decisions made by private sector led sectorial council; 
1.2/ Absence of decisions implemented by the sectorial councils; 
1.3/ Limited number of proposals initiated by farmers led extension boards; 
1.4/ Limited number of farmers’ extension board decisions considered by A-VET providers;
2.1/ Limited number of PPPs in A-VET and AE delivery;
2.2/ During the first phase project served 10’000 farmers; 1;500 students; 
2.3/ Four Farmers’ Extension Boards are operational so far;
3.1/ Currently project has up to 50 WBL graduates per year; 
3.2/ Number of students involved with the partner A-VET colleges is up to 300 annually;  
3.3/ Up to 250 students graduate A-VET programs annually; 
3.4/ Partner extension providers service up to 2400 farmers annually;  

Output:

